cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.CE, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the use of Turing's representation scheme for achieving artificial intelligence, which falls under the category of computational neuroscience (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SY). The unconventional substrate used in the study is networks of Belousov-Zhabotinsky vesicles, which is related to the field of engineering and technology (cs.ET) and chemical engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of Boolean functions in the recurrent networks, which is related to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
